<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 23 at 6:02PM MDT  by NWS Glasgow</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of northwestern Daniels
and northeastern Valley Counties through 700 PM MDT...
At 601 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 27
miles west of Opheim, moving east at 40 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 30 mph and small hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Opheim, Richland, Port Of Opheim, Thoeny and Glentana.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...30 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
